  "shortBio": "Nils Riber Blume (1909-01-20 - ) was a practicing physician in Gothenburg, Sweden. He was born in Lysekil as the son of the city physician Riber B. and Elin Maria Högberg. He graduated from Uddevalla in 1927, completed medical studies in Uppsala in 1930, and received a medical license there in 1935. Blume started his career as an assistant physician at Sahlgren's Hospital surgical department in 1936 and later worked at various medical institutions. In 1942, he began practicing as a physician in Gothenburg. He was also a temporary assistant dispensary physician in Gothenburg for about six months in 1944-46."  
